cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing the language complexity of English texts from Wikipedia.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely category as the paper involves analyzing and comparing different samples of Wikipedia articles.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses statistical analysis to compare the language complexity of different samples.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper investigates the relation between conflict and language complexity in Wikipedia articles.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper analyzes the content of talk pages associated with controversial and peacefully developing articles.
